The paper presents a computational system that leverages perceptual algorithms to automatically create an ontology of relational structures and retrieve analogs from long-term memory. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.LG. The system also uses feature bags to represent relational structures, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval and database systems, falling under the sub-category of cs.CC. Finally, the system uses perceptual algorithms, which are often used in computer vision and image processing, falling under the sub-category of cs.CV.
